jobs.description:
Would you like to learn about investment funds and their corporate events?
We are looking for an intern for Funds Admin to:
• support in the registration and updating of investment funds with the regulatory bodies (cvm, anbima, b3 and receita federal);
• analysis and control of regulations, manuals and codes issued by regulatory bodies;
• meeting internal and external client demands;
• controlling cvm and anbima regulatory deadlines;
• control and operationalization of fund corporate events with counterparties;
• support in opening, updating and closing accounts
• identify and recommend ways to improve processes, reduce risks and strengthen controls
• ensure compliance with legal, regulatory and statutory requirements and with internal policies and contracts (e.g. supplier risk framework, gcoo operational risk framework).
• execute the processes and controls for which you are responsible in a timely, accurate and complete manner.
• attest to the quality of attribute data, so that our end consumers can rely on the quality of incoming.

